# campaign-journey-flows

Campaign Journey Orchestration Core (Importance: 95/100)

1. Journey Step Types
- Trigger nodes: Entry points based on user actions or events
- Delay nodes: Time-based wait periods with timezone optimization
- Condition nodes: Branching logic based on user attributes/behavior
- Action nodes: Email, SMS, webhook executions
- Exit nodes: Journey completion handlers

2. Journey State Management 
- Draft: Initial creation and configuration
- Active: Live journey processing audience members
- Paused: Temporary hold on new entries
- Archived: Historical record with performance data

3. Multi-Channel Sequencing Rules
- Channel cooldown periods between touchpoints
- Cross-channel frequency capping
- Priority-based channel selection
- Fallback channel configuration

4. Performance Optimization
- Real-time completion rate monitoring
- Step-level conversion tracking
- Audience segment performance analysis
- A/B test integration points

5. Journey Analytics
- Step-level metrics:
  - Entry rate
  - Completion rate
  - Time in step
  - Branch distribution
- Overall journey performance:
  - Total completion rate
  - Average journey duration
  - Revenue attribution
  - Engagement scoring

Critical Files:
/src/journeys/
- journey-builder.tsx: Core journey creation/editing
- journey-analytics.tsx: Performance tracking
- journey-automation.tsx: Execution engine
- journey-templates.tsx: Pre-built journey patterns

Business Rules:
- Maximum 25 steps per journey
- 72-hour minimum between promotional messages
- Geographic send time optimization
- Dynamic channel selection based on user preferences
- Automated journey pause if completion rate drops below 15%

